25|$|A {{good example}} of its {{replacement}} was the refitting of the Doolittle Raiders with a simple <b>iron</b> <b>sight.</b> Designed by Capt. C. Ross Greening, the sight was mounted to the existing pilot direction indicator, allowing the bombardier to make corrections remotely, like the bombsights of an earlier era.|$|E
